$interpreted: Guesthouse Boss: Ah! Please don't kneel! If you mess up your knees, how will you serve our guests?
Guesthouse Boss: Look at you, so busy you didn't even come to mail day! I suppose I'll give you your letter in person.
Beyata: Thank you, Boss, you are too good to me.
Guesthouse Boss: Your grandfather caught a bit of a cold these past few days, but he should be on his feet again soon enough.
Guesthouse Boss: These things happen when you get older. It all takes time and rest. You just need to have patience.
Beyata: Yes, I know... And I will work hard until he is all better.
Beyata: Patience, hmm? Yes, the boss is right.
Beyata: ………
Guesthouse Staff: Welcome, Master Orisuke.
Beyata: You don't look well, Master Orisuke. Is something the matter?
Orisuke: Yesterday I... I heard news that Eika Textiles have bribed the board to vote for them during next month's bid...
Orisuke: After all the time I took to import materials and research new styles... The arbiter was taking notice, but now they just take it all out from under me!!
Orisuke: I'm sorry, it's unbecoming of me to yell like this, I'm just so...
Beyata: Don't worry, Master Orisuke, I am here for you. I will do my best to help!
Orisuke: If I had enough money I might be able to turn the board's head, but I don't have nearly enough...
Beyata: ...I may have a way.
Beyata: Ever since you told me that I bring others happiness, well...
Beyata: I've been saving up some money, so that I might be able to help you one day!
Orisuke: W-What? Bluebird, really?
Beyata: Yes, really. Now, take this... I hope it can bring you happiness.
Orisuke: Thank you, Bluebird! Of course it will help! Thank you so much!
Orisuke: ...Once we get out of this town, I promise I'll make you the most beautiful outfit you've ever seen!
Orisuke: New clothes, new sights, good food... I'll show you the world, Beyata!
Beyata: The world~ Wow, I can't wait!
Beyata: What is this?
Orisuke: The bid is soon, I fear I won't be able to see you here for a short while. In the meantime, this dagger will protect you while I cannot.
Orisuke: If anyone tries to cheat you, don't be afraid! I'm with you in spirit!
Beyata: (Don't be afraid, I'm with you in spirit...)
Beyata: (I cannot stand by while others cheat Master Orisuke out of his own business. I must help him... for our future!)
Fashionable Guest: You want to put in an order with Eika Textiles? I wouldn't bother, sweetie, the bigger they get the worse their quality. And higher the prices!
Fashionable Guest: And I'm only tellin' you this 'cause you're cute, but... I heard they've got the Alliance backin' them up.
Beyata: (Hmm... If they're in with the elites, then I'll have to find someone even more elite to help.)
Beyata: Yagh, ow!
Beyata: W-What happened!? Are you okay!?
Surprised Girl: ─Bluebird!? Please, save me, Bluebird!
Surprised Girl: I can't take it anymore!
Guesthouse Boss: Hey, you can't run away while you're in the middle of serving a guest! Get back in there!!
Surprised Girl: Yaaaagh────!!
Guesthouse Boss: Don't make me say it again! This guest is a VIP, serving him is an honor!
Guesthouse Boss: I'm am very sorry, my good sir. She is merely tired and out of sorts, I shall bring her back to your room immediately!
Rich Guest: Well hurry up, this is killin' the mood!
Guesthouse Boss: Ah, yes, of course!
Beyata: (Wow, even the Boss is being so polite to this guest... who is he?)
Surprised Girl: ...P-Please, no! That guest is too rough, he's too scary! I can't! Please save me, Bluebird!
Beyata: Scary? I think he looks like a perfect gentleman.
Guesthouse Boss: Ah, this is our top girl, Bluebird~ Soft, warmhearted, very accomodating... do you like her, my good sir?
Rich Guest: Yes, I'll take this one, not that brat who ran off.
Beyata: ......Very well.
: One week later...
Beyata: ...Eh... yagh... Is it... over?
Rich Guest: You passed out for a bit there, but you lasted way longer than any of the other girls.
Rich Guest: Not bad... I'd say I'm satisfied. What do you want in return?
Beyata: ...In return? Your company alone is reward enough, Master.
Rich Guest: Eh, why are you crying? Somethin' wrong?
Beyata: No, it's just... been such an honor being together with you...
Beyata: But I'm afraid, one day, someone might come along and buy me away from you!
Rich Guest: What!? I'd like to see them try! Ain't nobody gonna take a broad out from under my nose!
Beyata: B-But, I heard... there was a textile-company owner who planned to purchase me from the guesthouse...
Rich Guest: Oh yeah? Who is it?
Beyata: Oh, I am but a humble servant, I couldn't say...
Beyata: I just know they are quite connected, they are even backed by the Alliance...
Rich Guest: Oh yeah? There aren't too many in textiles that have backing from the Alliance themselves.
Rich Guest: ─That son of a gun!
Rich Guest: Thinks he can come messin' around on my turf!?
Rich Guest: I guess it's time I pay him a visit.
Rich Guest: Maybe I'll make him an outfit of his own... dyed with his blood!
